  ## Summary                                                                  
                                                                              
  I fixed the 4 problematic EquivalentClass axioms that were causing          
  unsatisfiable classes in EFO. All changes were made to                      
  src/ontology/components/efo_equivalent_class_axioms.owl:                    
                                                                              
  ### Changes Made:                                                           
                                                                              
  1. **EFO_****0000792 (craniofacial tissue)** — Removed the self-referential 
  equivalence:                                                                
      • ~~EquivalentClasses(EFO_0000792 part_of some EFO_0000792)~~           
      • This circular definition caused anything part of craniofacial tissue  
      to be inferred as craniofacial tissue (itself an anatomical structure), 
      creating circular reasoning unsats.                                     
  2. **EFO_****0001958 (joint component)** — Added anatomical_structure to the
  intersection:                                                               
      • Before: EquivalentClasses(EFO_0001958 part_of some UBERON_0000982)    
      • After: EquivalentClasses(EFO_0001958                                  
      ObjectIntersectionOf(UBERON_0000061 part_of some UBERON_0000982))       
      • Without anatomical_structure, immaterial entities (like cavities) that
      are part of a skeletal joint would be classified as joint components    
      (material) → unsat.                                                     
  3. **EFO_****0001986 (lung structure)** — Added anatomical_structure to the 
  intersection:                                                               
      • Before: EquivalentClasses(EFO_0001986 part_of some UBERON_0002048)    
      • After: EquivalentClasses(EFO_0001986                                  
      ObjectIntersectionOf(UBERON_0000061 part_of some UBERON_0002048))       
      • Same fix as above.                                                    
  4. **EFO_****0003858 (skeleton structure)** — Removed the overly broad      
  equivalence:                                                                
      • ~~EquivalentClasses(EFO_0003858 part_of some UBERON_0001434)~~        
      • The correct definition (anatomical_structure AND part_of some         
      skeletal_system) already exists in efo-edit.owl. The removed version    
      forced all entities part of the skeletal system to be material          
      anatomical structures, including immaterial cavities → unsat.           
  5. Added Declaration(Class(obo:UBERON_0000061)) required by the new         
  intersection axioms.

